00:00:17.180 --> 00:00:17.690
hammer.

00:00:17.690 --> 00:00:21.810
And from the way it's been described, it
certainly sounds to me like he's fallen

00:00:21.810 --> 00:00:23.360
foul of a software bug

00:00:23.360 --> 00:00:26.830
which unfortunately has led him to, well,
have all of his

00:00:26.830 --> 00:00:30.910
PlayStation account banned which unfortunately includes his PlayStation 3 his PlayStation 4 and

00:00:30.910 --> 00:00:31.950
his PlayStation Vita.

00:00:31.950 --> 00:00:34.989
So let's quickly run through what happened to this poor chap.

00:00:34.989 --> 00:00:38.559
So he was playing Final Fantasy 10 on his 
PlayStation 3

00:00:38.559 --> 00:00:42.739
and his friend asked him to chat. So instead of coming out of the  game and into

00:00:42.739 --> 00:00:46.499
the chat system he got his Vita and was going to chat

00:00:46.499 --> 00:00:50.589
using that. Now his Vita asked him to run
an update and that's where his problems

00:00:50.589 --> 00:00:51.239
started.

00:00:51.239 --> 00:00:55.019
When he had run the update and it logged  back in  it

00:00:55.019 --> 00:00:58.199
then when he tried to go to the chat system  asked him to log back in again in. In

00:00:58.199 --> 00:01:00.249
attempting to log back in on his Vita

00:01:00.249 --> 00:01:04.239
it then said his account had been banned. He
thought, oh, that's really unusual maybe

00:01:04.239 --> 00:01:04.600
it's a

00:01:04.600 --> 00:01:07.920
glitch so he logged out on his PS3, tried to login

00:01:07.920 --> 00:01:11.969
and was banned. And having spoken to Sony  he has

00:01:11.969 --> 00:01:16.009
a rather interesting story really. To begin with  they basically

00:01:16.009 --> 00:01:17.340
said that he's been banned

00:01:17.340 --> 00:01:21.170
and he's been permanently banned for invalidation of terms of service.

00:01:21.170 --> 00:01:24.840
Now his friend spoke to Sony who then gave
a slightly different story

00:01:24.840 --> 00:01:29.000
saying that it might very well have been the PS Vita update

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:32.109
and he should try taking out his memory card
reinstalling the update and seeing if

00:01:32.109 --> 00:01:35.229
that makes a difference and  unfortunately that made no difference and

00:01:35.229 --> 00:01:39.210
he's still permanently banned. Now unfortunately Sony's customer service here seems to

00:01:39.210 --> 00:01:39.549
be

00:01:39.549 --> 00:01:44.450
absolutely useless I think I would say.
Given the scenario we're dealing with here.

00:01:44.450 --> 00:01:48.609
Run firmware update, attempt to login,
permanently banned immediately

00:01:48.609 --> 00:01:53.329
